{
  "uuid": "b26f16e789a8347980ca900a2d4623c7",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Trust Accounting Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the role</strong><br />We are seeking a talented and detail-oriented Trust Accounting Manager to join our team. In this full-time role, you will be responsible for providing comprehensive accounting and reporting services to our diverse portfolio of trust accounts, ensuring accurate and timely financial information for our clients.<br /></p><p><strong>What you'll be doing</strong></p><ul><li><p>Perform accurate and timely recording of all financial transactions related to trust accounts</p></li><li><p>Prepare periodic financial statements, including balance sheets, income statements, and cash flow reports for trust accounts</p></li><li><p>Reconcile trust account balances, including bank, investment, and other asset and liability accounts</p></li><li><p>Assist with the preparation of annual tax returns and other regulatory filings for trust accounts</p></li><li><p>Liaise with clients, investment managers, and other stakeholders to provide financial information and address inquiries</p></li><li><p>Maintain comprehensive documentation and filing systems for all trust account records</p></li><li><p>Identify and recommend process improvements to enhance the efficiency and accuracy of trust accounting operations</p></li></ul><p><strong>What we're looking for</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor's degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field, Chartered Accountant preferred</p></li><li><p>4-5 years of experience in trust accounting, investment accounting, or a similar financial reporting role</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of trust accounting principles, procedures, and applicable regulations</p></li><li><p>Prior experience in public and private market securities, fund accounting and knowledge of SFRS/IFRS is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Proficient in the use of accounting software and spreadsheet applications</p></li><li><p>Excellent attention to detail and problem-solving skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and as part of a team to meet deadlines</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and customer service skills</p></li></ul>",
